# Photometry, RV, ephemeris, and stellar-atmosphere/filter data files.
# GitHub's linguist classifier misidentifies these numeric data tables as
# Roff (no recognized extension -> falls back to a content classifier that
# false-positives on whitespace/number-heavy text), which is why the repo
# language stats showed ~92% Roff / ~8% Python instead of reflecting the
# actual Python codebase. Mark them vendored so they're excluded from stats.
*.dat linguist-vendored
*.rv linguist-vendored
*.eph linguist-vendored
*.filter linguist-vendored
*.WISE linguist-vendored
*.GAIA linguist-vendored
*.2MASS linguist-vendored
*.ascii linguist-vendored
examples/**/*.txt linguist-vendored
src/exozippy/components/sed/filters/** linguist-vendored
src/exozippy/components/sed/models/** linguist-vendored
